# Documentation hierarchy

## Read order

1. **`docs/README.md`**
2. **`principles/UNIVERSAL.md`** before UI changes in any consumer repo
3. **`docs/CONSUMPTION.md`** when wiring a product repo

## Single sources

| Topic | Canonical |
|-------|-----------|
| Tokens | `tokens/foundation.json`, `tokens/themes/*.json` |
| Patterns | `patterns/` + live site |
| Voice / copy | `voice/` + live site |
| ADRs | `adr/DESIGN_ADR.md` |
| Deploy reference site | `docs/DEPLOY_DOCS_SITE.md` |
| Cross-repo milestones | tasteful `docs/PLATFORM_MILESTONES.md` |

## Hard rules

- Generated artifacts (`dist/`, `swift/Sources`, npm package) must match `npm run build` output.
- Web-only product repos (Keystone, intrinsic-www) consume npm only — **no submodule**.
- tasteful keeps `design/` submodule for iOS SPM; all web apps use GitHub Packages.
- Do not fork token JSON in product repos.
- Live site is the human-friendly view; this repo is the machine source.
